	read using the DateTimeOriginal and SubsecTimeOriginal tags for
	subsecond precision

2007-03-01  Nicolas Roussel  <roussel@lri.fr>

	* nucleo/image/Image.*: 
	If the timestamp is undefined, getTimeStamp tries to load it from
	the image's metadata (e.g. EXIF tags)
	
	* nucleo/image/encoding/CoreGraphics.*: 	
	Renamed cg_calcdims to cg_decode_meta as it now updates the
	timestamp as well

	* nucleo/image/source/nucImageSource.cxx: 
	Notify observers when the source stops by itself

	* nucleo/helpers/OpenCV.H: 
	Images in any encoding other than ARGB, RGB or L will now be
	converted to ARGB instead of RGB

